Shoprite Workers in Zambia May End 3-Day Strike After Government Talks

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-03-30T16:10:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/shoprite-workers-in-zambia-may-end-3-day-strike-after-government-talks.html
Shoprite Holdings Ltd. (SHP)  workers in
Zambia, who have been on strike for three days over pay, may
return to work tomorrow, a labor union official said.  “We have made progress today after a long meeting chaired
by Mr Amon Chibunda, the Permanent Secretary of Labor, who
represented the minister and we may start work tomorrow,” Seth
Paraza, general secretary of the National Union of Commercial
and Industry Workers, said by phone today from Lusaka, the
capital.  Employees at Shoprite,  Africa ’s largest food retailer that
operates 18 stores in the southern African country, want
an increase in the minimum monthly wage, a better pension and 
for workers to be given permanent jobs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
